Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of Max 2CSP-$R$, which involves finding an assignment to variables that maximizes the number of satisfied constraints. This problem is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of semidefinite programming (SDP) and novel rounding technique suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper's focus on approximation algorithms and the Unique Games Conjecture suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT).
